Praying for Ukraine 🇺🇦
Speak, stand and spread awareness for those that can’t 💔 It’s very important for us to say something and not ignore what is going on even if it’s half way across the world. It’s our due diligence as humans to acknowledge what’s happening. Hope this nightmare, chaos and senseless cowardliness ends soon. 
⠀
How you can Help.
⠀
💙 Use your Platform to spread awareness
⠀
💙 https://www.care.org/
“Families in Ukraine are fleeing violence and urgently need emergency aid. CARE is providing food, water, and more,”
⠀
💙 https://www.doctorswithoutborders.org
Doctors Without Borders, which works in conflict zones, is partnering with volunteers in Ukraine to help people travel to health-care facilities and working to ensure people have access to health care and medicine.
⠀
💙 https://www.globalgiving.org/
a U.S.-based nonprofit launched its Ukraine Crisis Relief Fund page, stating that all donations to the fund will support humanitarian assistance in impacted communities in Ukraine and surrounding regions where Ukrainian refugees have fled.

It's so atrocious what is happening in Ukraine. I can't believe this is going on in the 21st century. The human race has not learned anything from the past :( Help if you can, Doctors Without Borders are awesome and your donation will go a long way. 

www.doctorswithoutborders.org

We are heartbroken by the unnecessary human suffering and loss of life in Ukraine. As a wellness company, we stand for peace and are here to support all of those in need.

Therabody is making a donation to Doctors Without Borders, an impartial organization committed to providing medical humanitarian assistance to people affected by war. They are stepping up their response to the deepening crisis in Ukraine and neighboring countries where more than two million refugees have fled.

As a company whose purpose is focused on building healthier communities, there has never been a more critical time to focus on providing access to emergency supplies and medical staff that provide a lifeline to those affected by war. For more information about @doctorswithoutborders or to make a donation, visit http://doctorswithoutborders.org. #StandWithUkraine

Yep…that’s the Ukrainian flag. You know blue and yellow are what makes the color green. While the King of the Leprechauns wanted me to share that color insight, I really want to reiterate my support for the incredibly tough Ukrainian people, who are suffering greatly and unnecessarily.  They are a huge inspiration.

Doctors Without Borders is one of the charitable organizations my company supports monthly. I am doubling my support to them this month in support of their perilous work in Ukraine.  Here is a link for those that wish to support their work. https://www.doctorswithoutborders.org/what-we-do/countries/ukraine

The Duke PA Program is collecting monetary donations for Medecins Sans Frontieres (Doctors Without Borders) to support their current mission in Ukraine. MSF is providing medical supplies, medical assistance, and additional support services. If you would like to read more about MSF’s presence in Ukraine using the link below.

Donations will be accepted via Venmo to @ ShianneWood (Vice President, Class of 2023) or @ ZoeCouse (IPEC SAC PA Representative, Class of 2023) until March 26th. The Duke PA Leadership Society will be graciously matching 20% of donations!

Find more information here:
https://www.doctorswithoutborders.org/what-we-do/countries/ukraine

The world seems to have changed with Ukraine. 
As we watch this horrific war unfold in Europe, we are full of feelings of fear and helplessness. However, in these dark days we know that we can still help with the vital relief efforts from wherever we are in the world by supporting Doctors without borders. 

If you are thinking of donating for Ukraine, please consider our charity of choice and visit https://www.doctorswithoutborders.org 
A small donation goes a long way, so we urge you to spread love….

❤️🇺🇦
